company
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANGUS FOSTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MR Robert Smialek has stepped down as chief operating officer of the
temperature and appliance controls division of Siebe, the engineering
company, writes Angus Foster.
Mr Smialek joined Siebe four years ago and became a main board director last
November. He is to become chairman and chief executive officer of Insilco,
the US automotive and consumer products group which recently emerged from
chapter 11 proceedings.
Mr Barry Stephens, Siebe's chairman, said Mr Smialek had been made an offer
'he just couldn't refuse'. 'He's going to have a salary you can choke on and
millions of share options,' he said.
