<TEXT>
A UN report on the conflict in the Caucasus falls short of alleging Armenian
government involvement in the latest fighting in Azerbaijan. Western
diplomats say it is unlikely to lead to a binding Security Council
resolution imposing sanctions on Armenia, reports John Murray Brown in
Ankara
The UN findings will come as a disappointment to Turkey, which has lobbied
for UN action to stop the fighting as Azerbaijan claimed Armenian forces had
seized 10 per cent of its territory.
The Armenian government has denied that its forces are involved.
