<HEADLINE>
FT  16 APR 93 / World Commodities Prices: Fruit and Vegetables
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Pineapples at Pounds 1.00-1.30 each (Pounds 1.00-1.30) are an excellent buy
this week, along with Bramley apples at 35-45p a lb (35-45p), Shamouti
oranges at 12-35p each (12-35p) and outdoor rhubarb at 25-35p a lb (25-35p),
reports FFVIB. Supplies of cauliflower are increasing and are in the shops
at 45-55p each (65-85p). Other good vegetable choices include Spring greens
at 35-40p a lb (35-40p), broccoli at 45-55p per 8oz pre-pack, English
potatoes at 10-14p a lb (10-14p) and carrots at 20-25p a lb (20-25p).
English and Dutch cucumbers are currently priced at 50-70p each (50-70p)
depending on size. Tomatoes are 60-99p a lb (55-90p).
</TEXT>
