FT  16 APR 93 / UK Company News: Risky contract helps Cradley reach Pounds
1.14m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Interim pre-tax profits of Cradley Group, the lithographic printer, surged
from Pounds 487,000 to Pounds 1.14m, but the result benefited from a large
one-off contract in a 'disappointing half year'.
Mr Donald Jordan, chairman, said the period to December 31 saw a shrinking
market for print, with profit margins virtually zero.
He said the one-off contract for Europe resulted in a considerable
over-recovery of costs. In terms of production schedule it was a high risk
contract, but the very tight schedule had been met.
The magazine printing business, he said, returned a loss of some Pounds
400,000 after tax.
Sales increased to Pounds 17.2m (Pounds 13.7m). Earnings per share were 2.3p
(1p).
