<HEADLINE>
FT  16 APR 93 / UK Company News: BP chief defends predecessor's pay-off
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Lord Ashburton, chairman of BP, has defended the Pounds 1.5m package of
compensation and pension payments made to Mr Robert Horton, his predecessor
who was ousted in a boardroom coup last summer.
He told the annual meeting that 'the figures are in absolute terms large,
and perhaps larger than are easily understood'. But, he said, the Pounds
780,000 paid in compensation was what Mr Horton could have expected to
receive in court proceedings if the company had not agreed to pay.
Some Pounds 723,000 was also made to the pension fund to ensure his pension
rights were fully funded.
</TEXT>
