<HEADLINE>
FT  16 APR 93 / Technology (Worth Watching): A testing mix for the drinks
industry
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DELLA BRADSHAW
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Many people have ordered an expensive brand of whisky or brandy in a bar
only to suspect that the bottle has been topped up with a lesser - and
cheaper - brand. What is bad news for the customer can be catastrophic news
for the drinks maker, as such tactics reduce its credibility.
To help traders ensure only their products are sold under their name,
Biocode of Nottingham has developed a marking system which can be added to
the liquor in just three or four parts per billion. Antibodies to these
markers are then developed which react with it - by changing colour. By
removing a trace of the liquor and mixing it with the antibodies it is
possible to tell if the drink has been tampered with. Biocode: UK, 0904
430616.
