FT  16 APR 93 / World News in Brief: Diet advice
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Advice to eat a low-fat diet to counter heart disease may not apply to
women, according to a 15-year study of more than 15,000 adults in Scotland.
The study found women were more likely than men to have high blood fat
levels but less likely to die of heart attacks.
